Gov Ahmadu Fintiri, has condemned in strong terms, the recent insurgency attack, on some communities in michika and madagali LGAs of Adamawa state. Recall that, the military have on Thursday evening repelled, attacks on Koppa and Maikadari of the two councils. An eye witness confirmed that, the insurgent storm the two villages by 6:30 PM, shooting sporadically in to the air and lotted shops. Humwashi Wonosikou, Press Secretary to the Governor in a statement also, commended the efforts of the military, local hunters and vigilante groups for repelling the attack. “Gov Fintiri is appealing for calm in the affected areas and is also on the top of the situation working in their interest. “It is in line with his Agenda on protecting lives and property that Gov Fintiri has secured operational vehicle for security in the state. “The vehicles, has put in place the operational apparatus code named “OPERATION FARAUTA” with a to making the state crime free”.